title: $:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/changelog
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.1.4 |2026-05-14 |Email attachments are now ''first-class''. With file-pipeline 0.1.10's per-output MIME inference + new `rimir-file-pipeline-artifact-created` hook, each non-inline attachment becomes a properly-typed tiddler (`application/pdf`, `application/vnd.ms-outlook`, …) instead of every output silently defaulting to `image/png`. The pipeline executor's nested-trigger startup picks each attachment up and re-runs its matching pipeline — a PDF attachment gets the PDF pipeline's thumbnail + text extraction; an attached `.msg` gets its own `.email` (recursively, unbounded with cycle protection via a `seen` map of URIs). doc/architecture, doc/examples, doc/faq updated with the new tiddler tree shape + recursion semantics. Pairs with file-upload 0.1.21's transitive cascade walk (delete + rename now cover the multi-level descendants too) and its delete-confirm modal (lists the full cascade + backlinks before nuking, opt-out via `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/confirm-deletes`). No code changes in this plugin — the fix lives in file-pipeline 0.1.10 / file-upload 0.1.21 |
|0.1.3 |2026-05-13 |Thumb rendering simplified to subject-only centred caption — the sender/date row was unreadable at thumb size and depended on a font with umlaut coverage. New `ViewTemplateBodyFilter` cascade (`cascade/msg.tid` + `body/msg.tid`) for `application/vnd.ms-outlook` tiddlers: shows the thumbnail in default view; clicking it switches to "full" view which transcludes the sibling `<title>.email` body (markdown rendered with frontmatter fields in place). Reuses file-upload's `$:/state/file-upload/view-mode/<title>` state for consistency with PDF/image expand-to-full behaviour. Fixes the parent `.msg` tiddler's default "Trying to load external content" fallback in TW's story river |
|0.1.2 |2026-05-13 |New thumbnail pipeline step (`msg-thumb` runner-action). Renders a 200×200 PNG via ImageMagick `caption:` showing the email subject above sender + date — sets `_thumbnail_uri` on the parent `.msg` tiddler. Gated by `$:/config/rimir/msg-import/thumb` (default `yes`). Sized from `$:/config/rimir/file-pipeline/thumb-resolution` (same as PDF/image thumbs). extract.py grows `--mode=thumb --input <msg> --output <png> --size <px>`. orga-apps 0.2.60 picks up the thumbnail and routes the click to the `.email` artifact |
|0.1.1 |2026-05-13 |Use `{{canonical_uri}}` (new in file-pipeline 0.1.9) for derived-file URLs instead of computing them from the filesystem path. Fixes broken inline-image refs when dropping into orga-apps (or any non-`/files/` location) — those locations have a `uriPrefix` distinct from their `basePath`, so the filesystem-relative path was not a valid served URL. extract.py now takes `--source-uri` and derives URLs as `<dirname(source_uri)>/_derived/<basename(source_uri)>/<filename>`, percent-encoded |
|0.1.0 |2026-05-13 |Initial release: pipeline tiddler matching `application/vnd.ms-outlook`, Python extractor (`scripts/extract.py`) emitting YAML frontmatter + markdown via pandoc, attachment + inline-image extraction with cid: rewriting, executable-attachment quarantine, optional LLM summary step (off by default). Extractor handles file-pipeline's `path.resolve()` stripping the trailing slash on `output` (body mode: `--attach-dir` always treated as the destination directory; attachments mode: split into dirname + basename-prefix for scanDir match). URLs percent-encoded so tiddler titles with spaces survive CommonMark image-link parsing |
